The Holodomor, a famine that occurred in Ukraine in 1932 and 1933, resulted in the suffering and death of millions of innocent Ukrainians. This article pays tribute to the victims and condemns the brutal policies of Joseph Stalin's regime. It calls for preventing similar tragedies in the future and supporting those currently suffering under tyrannical rule. The article also acknowledges the resilience of the Ukrainian people, who have overcome the horrors of the Holodomor and established a free and democratic society. The United States reaffirms its commitment to the people of Ukraine and their sovereignty and territorial integrity.